 Traditionalists have called on the Ogun State Government to review its land grabbing laws with a view to empowering the traditional institution to resolve land disputes. They said this was necessary to tackle the menace of land grabbing in different parts of the state which had led to disputes. The traditionalists made the call at a meeting with a real estate developer, Osokoya Adewale Morenikeji, at the palace of the Tami of Odogbolu, Oba Leke Oludipe, in Odogbolu LGA of the state. The meeting, which was attended by community leaders, chiefs, traditionalists and other stakeholders, was organised to find a lasting solution to the crises associated with land grabbing in the state.